<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Wenatchee, Washington 3/9/2002<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.94)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9268'>Mike "the Mad Maia" French</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=9268&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> March 12, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> Being the first Lord of the Rings tournament in Wenatchee, this was a big event.  My brother Ryan French and I, living 1 1/2 hours away in Ellensburg, had been preparing for weeks, playtesting and tweaking our decks.  But then the announcement was made that this was to be a multi-player format tourney.  My brother, playing nazgul and gandalf elves, didn&#39;t like his chances going in, even after trying to adjust his deck for multi.  I, on the other hand, had a Moria machine, with my new rare merry, assisted by uncommon Boromir and Aragorn, leading the way.  Before the tourney, we counted up only 8 players (we had hoped for around 12), filled out command cards, traded, bought packs, etc.  Our new tournament director, Dennis Jeffris, explained the format, pairings, and prizes.  The entry fee was $10 a person (which is a bit much), but it was worth it, as first place was 20 bucks, second 10, and third 5.  plus everyone was given one fellowship booster before the tourney, and we got 3 or 4 pizzas during the break between 2nd and 3rd rounds.<br>
<br>
First round: two four player games, Me, my bro Ryan, Tom Potter, and Dennis.  Dennis had a nasty uruk hai deck with greenleaf and aragorn w/bow keeping his fellowship truckin&#39;.  Tom was the guy i was worried about though.  He had a Moria machine just like me, only he had some nasty support cards that i didnt, like the cave troll&#39;s chain and 4 frickin&#39; goblin armories (i only have 1).  Bid: I bid 3, Ryan 2, Dennis 1, Tom none.  (or maybe dennis bid none and tom bid one, i cant remember).  I choose first, Ryan goes 2nd, then Dennis and finally Tom.  I surprise everyone with the Green Dragon Inn, depriving them of their precious Aragorn.  I start Boromir, SOD and rare Merry, pull Sam, dont get Aragorn in my starting hand, and pray that i survive the next 2 sites.  Unfortunately, i was stopped at site 2 by some nasty bad guys.  The game progresses, Ryan gets beat up bad on his first couple turns, Gandalf is dead (which his deck is based around), Dennis doesnt do so hot, and Tom is doin a&#39;ight.  I&#39;m holding a steady third.  But my cave troll is leading the way, appearing three times in the first game, all 3 times holding his hammer (thanks to relics of moria).  I barely stumble to site six, where i heal almost all my wounds, and finally get aragorn and his sword out.  i then move, and am faced by the cave troll&#39;s keyward and his ugliness himself, complete with hammer AND chain.  20 power, damage +2.  i cant remember, but i think i ranger&#39;s versatilitied him.  but anyway, the troll had 2 or 3 wounds somehow.  so i put him against aragorn w/ ranger&#39;s sword.  boromir takes care of his other minion, then exerts twice to make merry (with hobbit sword) strength +6, then merry exerts twice to add 11 to aragorn&#39;s power.  Aragorn: 21.  Cave Troll: 20.  i killed the cave troll.  let me say that again: I KILLED THE CAVE TROLL!!!!!  i actually stood up and shouted this for everyone to hear.  this, for me, was the turning point.  i moved again.  time was almost gone.  i survived.  i moved again.  i was ahead of everyone, and i had aragorn and frodo left (with only 2 burdens).  then it came to ryan&#39;s turn.  with 5 minutes left in the game, he played aragorn and moved three times to catch up to me (without gandalf, mind you), and because his frodo had no burdens, he won the game cause of the first tiebreaker.  his companions were all exhausted, and there was no way he would&#39;ve won, but we ran out of time.  he robbed me.  so i was a bit upset.  Ryan 1st, Me 2nd, Dennis 3rd, Tom 4th (my cave troll wasn&#39;t very nice to tom).  <br>
+4 points for second place (timed-out)<br>
<br>
Second Round: Me, Ryan, Ian, Nick.  i bid 4, i go first and play the green dragon inn to piss off everyone else.  this worked perfectly.  i drew aragorn in my starting hand, got his sword the next turn, and there was no stopping me.  i won handily.  the cave troll came out and bruised up some people, and aragorn, boromir, and merry were a powerhouse.  i even beat back the balrog with aragorn (and merry&#39;s help) and moved right past him to the sanctuary.  full win, +7 victory points.  ryan did just fine, but he wasnt as fast as my fellowship, and he came in second, with ian and nick getting 3rd and 4th.  <br>
+7, 11 total.<br>
<br>
we then took a short break.  good pizza (the card shop is next door to a pizza place).  i bought a cherry coke and the lid said win a free cherry coke, it was just my lucky day.<br>
<br>
after two rounds, ryan and i were tied with 11, couple guys had 9, and the rest were down in the basement.<br>
<br>
third round: Me, Ryan, Nick and Dennis.  Two brothers vs. two brothers.  it was an awesome game.  i bid 4 and went first, dennis learned his lesson and started with aragorn instead of legolas and arwen.  green dragon inn pissed off nick.  i got aragorn fairly quickly, but dennis was off like a madman down the adventure path.  by the time i caught up to him, it was too late.  His uruk-hai messed up ryan bad, and my cave troll messed up nick bad.  dennis got aragorn&#39;s bow out and my moria minions dropped like flies.  dennis played a great game and won fairly easily.  i came in second at site 8, nick got 3rd, and ryan came in at 4th.  +5 points for me, total of 16.<br>
<br>
goin into the last round, 3 dudes were tied for 4th: nick, ryan, and ian, all with 12 points.  so we shuffled up the command cards and nick was the pick, goin against me (in first so far), dennis, and tom.  ryan and ian played against matt and eric (who were tied for last), and we figured out that if ryan or ian won their game, and nick got a timed win with dennis in second and me in third, then ryan or ian could actually win the tourney.  but i was pretty confident.  i bid 5 (good thing i changed my bid, cause nick bid 4), went first, got the green dragon inn, and moved one measley site and got stopped.  but everyone else went a little slow at first too, so i was lucky.  nick had trouble early, and dennis couldnt seem to get legolas or arwen out.  tom died early putting him in 4th place.  my merry machine kept me alive (barely) and i stumbled to site 6.  my next turn i got stopped at site 7.  fortunately, nick couldnt seem to keep companions alive, and dennis was exhausted and one site behind me.  at site 7 i drew my ranger&#39;s sword, blade of gondor, and a hobbit sword for frodo, got rid of most of my wounds, and moved on to site 8.  i was confronted by lurtz.  aragorn and a dagger strike (and merry) took care of him.  i moved to site 9.  i was confronted by a multitude of uruks, all fierce, including a troop of uruk-hai and an orthanc assassin.  but he had to exert them to make them fierce.  so i put the orthanc on boromir, and exerted boromir twice to wound the assassin twice, killing him.  aragorn took two wounds on the other dude, merry died, but i survived.  i won.  i couldnt believe it.  i won.  i&#39;d never played in a tournament before, star wars or lord of the rings.  and i won.  it was awesome.  so i got my prize money, bought some packs, and did some nice trades.  <br>
<br>
all in all, a great tourney.  everyone had a blast.  what more is there to say?  oh yah, dennis ran his first tourney as a tourney director, and he did an awesome job.  in fact, i would hafta say that he did a super-scrumcioulescent job.  looking forward to the next tourney!<br>
<br>
